The GPI2 gate is a single qubit gate representing a pi/2 pulse.

The unitary matrix of this gate is
$$
\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}}
\begin{bmatrix}
    1 & -i e^{-i \phi} \\
    -i e^{-i \phi} & 1
\end{bmatrix}
$$

See [IonQ best practices](https://ionq.com/docs/getting-started-with-native-gates){:external}.
